Quick code tutorial: Rerank text Last Updated : 2026-01-08 You can rank a list of documents or search results according to their relevance to a given query by using the watsonx APIs and SDKs. This tutorial demonstrates how to rerank text with a reranker foundation model. You can implement reranking in a retrieval-augmented generation pattern to rerank the top set of results that are retrieved by relevance instead of similarity. Work
          with Python, Node.js, or Curl. You can complete this tutorial in less than 5 minutes. Detailed information Rerank passages Reranker foundation models Retrieval-augmented generation Prerequisite Complete the one-time steps to gather your credentials and other information and prepare your system. See Prerequisite one-time tasks . Rerank text Python Node.js Curl To rerank text, add the following code to the example.py file. Replace {watsonx_ai_url} , {apikey} , and {project_id} with your values. from ibm_watsonx_ai import Credentials from ibm_watsonx_ai.foundation_models import Rerank import json

credentials = Credentials(
   api_key = "{apikey}" , 
   url = "<your-service-url>" )

rerank = Rerank(
   model_id = "cross-encoder/ms-marco-minilm-l-12-v2" ,
   credentials = credentials,
   project_id = "{project_id}" )

query = "As a Youth, I craved excitement while in adulthood I followed Enthusiastic Pursuit." inputs = [ "In my younger years, I often reveled in the excitement of spontaneous adventures and embraced the thrill of the unknown, whereas in my grownup life, I have come to appreciate the comforting stability of a well-established routine." , "As a young man, I frequently sought out exhilarating experiences, craving the adrenaline rush of lifes novelties, while as a responsible adult, I have come to understand the profound value of accumulated wisdom and life experience." ]

result = rerank.generate( query = query, inputs = inputs) print ( json.dumps( result[ "results" ], indent= 3 ) ) Copy to clipboard Sample output: [
   {
      "index": 0,
      "score": 0.0997525081038475
   },
   {
      "index": 1,
      "score": -1.6803983449935913
   }
] To rerank text, add the following code to the example.js file. Replace {apikey} and {project_id} with your values. const { IamAuthenticator } = require( "ibm-cloud-sdk-core" );
const { WatsonXAI } = require( "@ibm-cloud/watsonx-ai" );

const authenticator = new IamAuthenticator( { "apikey" : "{apikey}" } );

const query = "As a Youth, I craved excitement while in adulthood I followed Enthusiastic Pursuit." ;

const inputs = [
   { "text" : "In my younger years, I often reveled in the excitement of spontaneous adventures and embraced the thrill of the unknown, whereas in my grownup life, I've come to appreciate the comforting stability of a well-established routine." },
   { "text" : "As a young man, I frequently sought out exhilarating experiences, craving the adrenaline rush of life's novelties, while as a responsible adult, I've come to understand the profound value of accumulated wisdom and life experience." }
];

watsonxAI_service.textRerank( { "query" : query, "inputs" : inputs, "parameters" : { "return_options" : { "top_n" : 2 } }, "modelId" : "cross-encoder/ms-marco-minilm-l-12-v2" , "projectId" : "{project_id}" } ). then ( ( response ) => {
  console.log( JSON.stringify( response.result.choices[0], null, 3 ) );
} ); Copy to clipboard Sample output: {
      " index ": 0,
      " score ": 0.2686532437801361
   },
   {
      " index ": 1,
      " score ": -1.575758934020996
   }
] To rerank text: Create a JSON file with the following content. Replace {project_id} with your value. "query" : "As a Youth, I craved excitement while in adulthood I followed Enthusiastic Pursuit." , "inputs" : [
